text: Franziska Koch (born 13 July 2000 in Mettmann) is a German cyclist, who currently rides for UCI Women's WorldTeam . Koch started up her career in local club RV Edelweiss Mettmann 1906 in 2010. In 2016 she won second place in junior national track championships on the Omnium. In 2017 she returned to win the Omnium national title. That year, she also won the Cross Country national title in mountainbiking, and came third in the national junior road championships. ==Major results== ;2019 : 4th Overall Festival Elsy Jacobs ::1st Young rider classification : 1st stage 4 Boels Ladies Tour ==References== ==External links== * Category:2000 births Category:Living people Category:German female cyclists Category:People from Mettmann
